<div class="article__hgroup">
<a href="/1747141/martin-fritz-huber" class="cluster-link upper space-half--btm dib font--sans text--s ls--2" data-ga-event-category="cluster-eyebrow" data-ga-event-on="click" data-ga-event-action="click" data-ga-event-label="/1747141/martin-fritz-huber" data-amplitude-internal-source="cluster eyebrow"><strong>In Stride</strong></a> <h1 class="article__title heading__one js-article-title">The Quarantine Backyard Ultra Is Perfectly Insane</h1>
<h2 class="article__subtitle subtitle">It’s an isolated struggle against an invisible adversary for an indefinite amount of time. Sound familiar?</h2>
</div>
</header>
<div class="article__hero enlarge js-open-modal" data-modal-img-src="https://www.outsideonline.com/sites/default/files/styles/img_1400x800/public/2020/04/07/mike-wardian-backyard_h.jpg?itok=2xr14mzv">
<div class="article__photo-meta">
<span class="article__caption">Ultrarunner Mike Wardian won the first (and, hopefully, only) Quarantine Backyard Ultra, by running 262.5 miles.</span> <span class="article__credit">(<em>Photo: </em>Courtesy Stephen Gosling)</span> </div>
<div class="article__hero-image article__hero-image--has-blur">
